title: BMW i8 Standard
description:
The BMW i8 is a plug-in hybrid (PHEV) sports car developed by BMW's i division.
- Carbon Fiber Cell: Built with a fully carbon cell, a feature typically exclusive to supercars.
- Aerodynamics: Drag coefficient (Cx) of 0.26
- Weight: 1,485 kg
- Power: Combined output of 362 hp
- Advantages: Lightweight, low center of gravity, and 154 hp per liter, the highest in BMW’s lineup at its launch
- Top Speed: Electronically limited to 250 km/h
- Acceleration: 0-100 km/h in 4.4 seconds; 80-120 km/h in 2.6 seconds
- Fuel Efficiency: 2.1 L/100 km

This is a future-forward car that will continue to turn heads for decades. Its design feels timeless and lightweight—qualities not found in most sports cars.

Design Highlights:
- Rear LED lights and front Laser headlights
- Numerous aerodynamic air diffusers, closed BMW kidney grille, and air intake on the hood
- Designed in a wind tunnel for optimal aerodynamics

Interior Features:
- Two LCD displays: a central screen with multimedia, navigation, vehicle settings, and onboard computer, plus a driver display that changes according to the selected driving mode, providing all relevant driving information
- Highly supportive and comfortable seats, crafted in perforated leather, heated, with multiple electric adjustments

Comfort and Safety Features:
- Dual-zone climate control, automatic headlights, automatic high beams, cruise control, and pre-collision assist
- Harman Kardon sound system
- 360-degree camera and front and rear parking sensors

Driving Experience:
- Very low, ergonomic, and sporty driving position close to the ground
- The electric motor provides near-instant torque, achieving 0-100 km/h in about 4.4 seconds, maintaining strong acceleration through gear shifts

Battery Charging:
- Approximately 3.5 hours on a standard outlet, or around 1.5 hours on a Type 2 charger.

The BMW i8 stands out as a unique combination of futuristic design, advanced technology, and high performance.
